    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1883-02-27T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1883-02-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="535" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d535">
                <head>No. 536.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Frelinghuysen</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Wallace</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1883-02-27">
                            <hi rend="italic">February</hi> 27,
                            1883</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 55.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your No.
                        168, of the 25th ultimo, reporting the outrage perpetrated by Armenians upon
                        the Rev. R. M. Cole, an American citizen, in the city of Erzingan, and your
                        action in immediately addressing the Turkish Government asking that the
                        offenders be punished.</p>
                <p>In approving your course as discreet and prompt, I have to add that it is
                        hoped the result will be immediate and satisfactory.</p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>FRED’K T. FRELINGHUYSEN.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
